Title: Long Term Potentiation, Navigation Dynamic Progamming  
Author: Peter Dayan Satinder Pal Singh 
Keyword: Preference: Oral Category: Theory and Analysis; Learning and Memory  
Address: Cambridge, MA 02139  1 Cambridge Center Cambridge, MA 02142  
Affiliation: MIT  Harlequin, Inc  
Pubnum: CBCL E25-210,  
Abstract: Blum and Abbott (1995) recently proposed an algorithm for learned navigation that is based on Hebbian changes to adaptive connections between place cells in the hippocampus. This paper suggests using a temporal difference rule (Sutton, 1988) for synaptic plasticity instead, and shows how this alters the resulting behaviour. It also recasts the problem of navigation into the reinforcement learning context of adaptive optimising control, and shows how to learn new trajectories that are not based only on averaging old ones. 
